Package: changepointSelect
Type: Package
Date: 2020-04-18
Title: Automated Selection of Changepoints using Empirical P-Values and Trimming
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Matthew", "Quinn", email = "mjq522@g.harvard.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Kimberly", "Glass", email = "kimberly.glass@channing.harvard.edu", role = "aut"))
Maintainer: Matthew Quinn <mjq522@g.harvard.edu>
Description: Uses an empirical p-value process to select the optimal set of changepoints among those suggested by running CROPS on PELT. Also performs a trimming process to remove false positives that arise due to linear trends and seasonal patterns.
Depends:
    changepoint,
    doParallel
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
